@startmindmap
* OAuth
** Grants
*** Authorization code grant type
****:Proof Key for Code Exchange (PKCE)
Allows authorization server to verify authorization
and token request came from the same client;
***[#red] Implicit grant type
****:Get tokens directly from authorization request
Originally for browser based public clients that
couldn't protect client secrets
Generally deprecated in favour of auth code + PKCE;
***[#red] Resource owner grant type
****:Client trades username + password for tokens
Generally deprecated because clients should not see
resource owner credentials;
*** Client credentials grant type
**** No resource owner\nExchange client ID + secret for tokens
*** Assertion grant type
****:Client is given a signed assertion it passes to
resource server in exchange for tokens;
@endmindmap
